(147, 1, '2015-03-16 13:40:53', '2015-03-16 19:40:53', '<h6>Experience</h6>\r\n10+ years in the Solar Industry\r\n20 years Business Development\r\n<h6>Education</h6>\r\nHarvard Business School, Masters of Business Administration\r\nBoise State University, Bachelors of International Business\r\n\r\nJason Ellsworth leads Clēnera as President and CEO. He and Adam Pishl founded the firm in July of 2013. Jason possesses a unique background in technology, solar, manufacturing, development, professional management and project finance that helps Clēnera operate as an end-to-end service provider in developing, acquiring and managing large-scale solar power assets. Together with Centaurus Renewable Energy and a very capable operating team at Clēnera, Jason and Adam ensure that the firm is rigorously managed, agile and responsive to business and project needs.\r\n\r\nPrior to launching Clēnera, Jason and Adam founded Sunlight Partners, a well-known developer of utility-scale solar energy plants. As CEO of Sunlight, he guided the development and commercialization of greater than 500 MW of solar generation projects across North America. Before Sunlight, Jason was Vice President and General Manager of U.S.-based solar manufacturer SolFocus. There, he developed the processes and manufacturing capability necessary to commercialize the SolFocus solar power generation product, including two highly automated manufacturing facilities. Jason worked at Corning prior starting the manufacturing business for SolFocus. At Corning he led product, technology and business development as Director of New Business Development for the company''s technical materials businesses. During his tenure at Corning Jason and his development teams created the Gorilla Glass and DLP optical packaging businesses. Together, these product lines generate over $1 Billion annually.   His efforts to support emerging solar companies such as First Solar and Mia-Sole sparked a passion for solar and renewables, leading to his departure from Corning in 2007 and launch of the business upon which SolFocus was built.', 'Jason Ellsworth', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jason-ellsworth', '', '', '2015-04-29 08:44:22', '2015-04-29 14:44:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/clenera/?post_type=team_member&#038;p=147', 0, 'team_member', '', 0),
(148, 1, '2015-03-16 13:40:35', '2015-03-16 19:40:35', '', 'jason', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'jason', '', '', '2015-03-16 13:40:35', '2015-03-16 19:40:35', '', 147, 'http://localhost/clenera/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/jason.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(152, 1, '2015-03-16 15:25:09', '2015-03-16 21:25:09', '<h6>Experience</h6>\r\n7+ years in the Solar Industry\r\n20+ years start-up operations and Project Management\r\n<h6>Education</h6>\r\nBoise State University, Masters of Business Administration\r\nBoise State University, Bachelors of Marketing\r\n\r\nAs Chief Operating Officer of Clēnera, Adam takes primary responsibility for systems and process management. He is focused on the rigorous stage-gate processes and documentation necessary to support project investment and long-term operations. Prior to Clēnera, he and Jason founded Sunlight Partners. At Sunlight, Adam was responsible for managing the innovative and unusually rigorous programmatic development process used by the company. Sunlight was the first to introduce technology development and management tools into the solar project development industry. As a result, Sunlight delivered a high volume (over 100) utility scale projects in the space of just 3 years.\r\n\r\nAdam also assembled a series of innovations and best practices in site identification and qualification to support rapid market development. Within one year his Sunlight development team identified, screened, and contracted greater than 60 utility-scale solar projects in North Carolina. The programmatic development model pioneered by Adam is now used by several successful solar developers in markets across North America.\r\n\r\nPrior to co-founding Sunlight Partners, Adam teamed up with Jason to create the glass business for SolFocus. As the Operations Manager at Solfocus Glass Works, Adam managed the development and operation of several high-volume technical processes, including a unique silver-plating line for concentrated solar photovoltaic optic lenses. He was responsible for design and construction of the prototype and eventual full capacity manufacturing lines and guided the operation to meet stringent ISO 9000 and other quality requirements. Adam and his team successfully implemented full-scale automation across the manufacturing platform for greater than 38 Megawatts of manufacturing capacity, while substantially increasing product performance and quality. He managed two operating facilities with greater than 140 employees.\r\n\r\nPrevious to SolFocus Adam led several small operating businesses in the construction, coatings, and manufacturing industries. His deep operational background and emphasis on process and controls helps assure strong performance across all Clēnera functional activities.', 'Adam Pishl', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'adam-pishl', '', '', '2015-04-27 14:58:23', '2015-04-27 20:58:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/clenera/?post_type=team_member&#038;p=152', 0, 'team_member', '', 0),
